Need to avoid com IBM specific code in BMC dump. dump-extension/openpower  path is used to keep all the codes speciifc com-ibm. Either use this or use new feature to enable the custom create function. Will wait for d-bus merge for final review.
In the latest PS, there are no changes to this file

Looks it is better to add it in the top level dump entry, so all types of dumps can use this interface
Refer previous comment related to todo

This should be 2 here. The same Macro. If originator type is passed, that will be the 2nd input parameter
Looks like common code used in two place , can you make this as utility function?
Still  seeing common code in multiple places.
Can you add a macro for this and use that macro here ?

Genaral design direction related: BMC dump manager supports various internal dump typesother than user type fault logs and internal d-bus interfaces.phosphor-debug-collector/xyz/openbmc_project/Dump/Internal/Create.interface.yaml .  What is the general direction you are planing follow here.
Some of the dumps are used internal create d-bus interface. It is better to be consistent in all types of dumps in from use case point.

So, now I have implemented this Originated interface in the bmc dump, system dump, and resource dump dbus object, for which user will be able to trigger (changes: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/38982/46) and create a dump, basically for all the user-generated dump types.
If the user generates the dump, then user details would be stored in the properties of this interface, else "Internal" would be stored (as I mentioned in https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-debug-collector/+/48337/6/dump_manager_bmc.cpp#238)
is this commit is going to enable by separate commit, Better to get This support also in place before merging this commit,
Okay, right now I haven't started on the persistance code for this field.

After application/bmc reboot , all these information is going to loose right?
Now seems to be alway's say's originated by internal and what is the no real use for this feature right after BMC/application reboot?

I anm working on persisting this property currently. I was planning to have a separate commit on top of this one, since it may also have more changes if put in the same commit.

Till then, can we have reviews and merge this change in?

I am ok with adding new commit , Since the complete functionality is broken  with out this support, i would prefer to merge both commit together.

Code looks good cleaner now also no new comments from my side.
why here setting to internal , be consistent on default behaviour.  incase user missed to provide the type other places your are setting to empty string.

No, earlier i set it to empty string. But now this originatorType is an enum. Unless we define "none" as an enum type, we must have one of the enum values as default. Hence, Internal was making sense there. If there is a bmc dump created, and if it is user-generated, this value would be Client, else, if it is not user-generated, this value would default to Internal.
Is this function throw any exception if no matching type is found? If it is throwing, please catch that too

Yes, it does throw sdbusplus::exception::InvalidEnumString.

Done
new parameters are not specified here
can this go into a generic file as i see this constant duplicated in multiple places
This is used only cpp files right? move to to cpp?
Std:: string default is empty , not null , better to initialize o_string with null here.

we are not setting it to null and cannot set it to null as it is not a pointer rather reference, just change the message.
"Originator id is not provided" is sufficient and it should be ERR type

std::string are initialized to empty string ("") automatically by default (default constructor).

empty() method checks if the length of the string is 0.

I have tested it -> irrespective of whether a string is initialized with "" or not, empty() returns true.
Same am also refering, but the log message is confusing , that is why added this comment. fix thelog  message.

if the type is not provided, then we are replacing it with the default. Just logging the same here
